                    </div>
                    <span>What is so cool about this book is that you can read it from start to finish and use it after as a reference book. The authors took a very difficult subject and made it easy to understand. After each chapter, you can code your own game with all the tips they gave you.<p>A must have if you want to start writing small games in C#.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Non-Intuitive development flow and glaring errors</div>
